claim.claim-text:
1. A semiconductor device comprising:
a substrate having a top surface, the substrate being formed of a first semiconductor material having a first lattice constant;
a first region comprising a first recess formed in the substrate and filled with a second semiconductor material, the second semiconductor material having a second lattice constant, the second semiconductor material extending above the top surface of the substrate and having a top surface;
a second region comprising a second recess formed in the substrate and filled with the second semiconductor material; and
an isolation region disposed between the first region and the second region, the isolation region having a first insulating layer and a second insulating layer, the first insulating layer extending into the substrate and having a horizontal top surface substantially coplanar with the top surface of the substrate, the second insulating layer being disposed directly on the horizontal top surface of the first insulating layer and extending above the top surface of the substrate, and sidewalls of the first insulating layer being coterminous with sidewalls of the second insulating layer;
wherein the first and second insulating layer of the isolation region comprise different materials.

13. A semiconductor device comprising:
a semiconductor substrate of a first semiconductor material having a first lattice constant, the semiconductor substrate having a top surface;
a gate electrode on the semiconductor substrate;
a first isolation region disposed in the semiconductor substrate, said first isolation region having a first insulation layer extending into the semiconductor substrate and having a horizontal top surface substantially coplanar with the top surface of the semiconductor substrate, and a second insulation layer disposed atop the horizontal top surface of the first insulation layer, the second insulation layer being elevated above the top surface of the substrate, wherein a first outermost edge of the first insulation layer is aligned with a first outermost edge of the second insulation layer, and wherein a second outermost edge of the first insulation layer is aligned with a second outmost edge of the second insulation layer, and wherein the first and second insulation layers comprise different materials;
a second isolation region disposed in the semiconductor substrate, said second isolation region having a third insulation layer extending into the semiconductor substrate and having a horizontal top surface substantially coplanar with the top surface of the semiconductor substrate and a fourth insulation layer disposed atop the top surface of said third insulation layer, the fourth insulation layer being elevated above the top surface of the substrate and having a planar top surface above the substrate, and wherein the third and fourth insulation layers comprise different materials;
a first active region disposed between the gate electrode and the first isolation region, the first active region comprising a first portion extending into the semiconductor substrate and a second portion elevated above the top surface, the second portion having a top surface;
a second active region disposed between the gate electrode and the second isolation region, the second active region comprising a third portion extending into the semiconductor substrate and a fourth portion elevated above the top surface, the fourth portion having a top surface; and
wherein the first and the second active region each comprises a second semiconductor material having a second lattice constant different from the first lattice constant of the first semiconductor material.
